<subSubSection id="C36DB7C1FFE1FFCDFF5AFC48FBAFABA9" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE1FFCDFF5AFC48FE8EA910" blockId="2.[160,1156,1005,1203]" box="[160,285,1005,1030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">
<heading id="D0805326FFE1FFCDFF5AFC48FE8EA910" box="[160,285,1005,1030]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" reason="5">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFF5AFC48FE8EA910" bold="true" box="[160,285,1005,1030]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" reason="3">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE1FFCDFF5AFBB5FDFAA9A5" blockId="2.[160,1156,1005,1203]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">
The genus name is a patronym, honouring the late emeritus professor of the University of 
<collectingRegion id="49B32AA8FFE1FFCDFF3FFB96FE80A95D" box="[197,275,1075,1099]" country="Iran" name="Tehran" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Tehran</collectingRegion>
Dr Mohammad Ebrahim Bastani Parizi (1924 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFCCEFB96FCD2A95D" box="[820,833,1075,1099]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">–</emphasis>
2014), who was an Iranian historian, translator, poet, essayist and author of non-fiction books. 
<materialsCitation id="3B1FEE17FFE1FFCDFC52FBF0FED2A9A5" country="Iran" location="Kerman" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kerman">
His numerous publications are mostly popular reads on the history of 
<collectingCountry id="F360A4DAFFE1FFCDFCFAFBDDFCB8A986" box="[768,811,1144,1168]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Iran</collectingCountry>
and the history of his hometown, 
<collectingRegion id="49B32AA8FFE1FFCDFF12FB3EFED2A9A5" box="[232,321,1179,1203]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Kerman</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE1FFCDFF5AFB41FE87A9EB" blockId="2.[160,1156,1252,1727]" box="[160,276,1252,1277]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFF5AFB41FE87A9EB" bold="true" box="[160,276,1252,1277]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" reason="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE1FFCDFF5AFAA2FBAFABA9" blockId="2.[160,1156,1252,1727]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFF5AFAA2FE95A809" authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[160,262,1287,1311]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFF5AFAA2FE95A809" box="[160,262,1287,1311]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Bastanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2308523FFE1FFCDFEF4FAA2FEE5A809" box="[270,374,1287,1311]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can easily be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFC5BFAA2FB80A809" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[929,1043,1287,1311]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hersiliidae</taxonomicName>
occurring in the region (
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFEB4FA8FFD20A854" authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[334,691,1322,1346]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Deltshevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFEB4FA8FFE2FA854" box="[334,444,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Deltshevia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE1FFCDFE33FA8FFD20A854" author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" box="[457,691,1322,1346]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFD3FFA8FFB83A854" authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[709,1040,1322,1346]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Duninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFD3FFA8FFC89A854" box="[709,794,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Duninia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE1FFCDFCDCFA8FFB83A854" author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" box="[806,1040,1322,1346]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFBD8FA8FFEBCA873" authority="Thorell, 1870" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFBD8FA8FFB10A854" box="[1058,1155,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Hersiliola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE1FFCDFF5AFAE8FEBCA873" author="Thorell T" box="[160,303,1357,1381]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" pagination="109 - 242" refId="ref5110" refString="Thorell T. 1870. On European spiders. Nova Acta Reg Soc Sci Upsaliensis. 7: 109 - 242." type="journal article" year="1870">Thorell, 1870</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFE93FAE8FD74A873" authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[361,743,1357,1381]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Ovtsharenkoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFE93FAE8FD90A873" box="[361,515,1357,1381]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Ovtsharenkoia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE1FFCDFDF6FAE8FD74A873" author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" box="[524,743,1357,1381]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), by short spinnerets, ovoid tegulum (not round), thick seminal ducts, large tegular apophysis, and very short and thick embolus. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFE70FA37FE63A8BC" authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[394,496,1426,1450]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFE70FA37FE63A8BC" box="[394,496,1426,1450]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Bastanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2308523FFE1FFCDFDFBFA37FDE2A8BC" box="[513,625,1426,1450]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
well differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFCB1FA37FC0CA8BC" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[843,927,1426,1450]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Duninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFCB1FA37FC0CA8BC" box="[843,927,1426,1450]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Duninia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFC10FA37FBCBA8BC" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[1002,1112,1426,1450]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Deltshevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFC10FA37FBCBA8BC" box="[1002,1112,1426,1450]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Deltshevia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the orientation of the tegular apophysis which is perpendicular to the cymbial axis (
<figureCitation id="134CF8CFFFE1FFCDFF5DFA72FEAFA8F9" box="[167,316,1495,1519]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,995,1018]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,956]" captionTargetId="figure-177@5.[163,1153,142,964]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Bastanius kermanensis sp. nov. (A, C) Male palp, ventral; (B) male palp, retrolateral; (D) epigyne, ventral; (E, F) epigyne, dorsal. Em, embolus; Be, base of embolus; Ta, tegular apophysis; Wi, window; Ag, accessory gland; Lr, lateral receptacle; Mr, mesal receptacle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206401/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Figures 2A− C</figureCitation>
); in the other two genera it is almost parallel to the cymbial axis (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE1FFCDFBD6FA72FECDAB04" author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik and Fet 2009: 87</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3.3−3.5). By the shape of the male palp, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFCACFA5FFC2FAB04" authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[854,956,1530,1554]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFCACFA5FFC2FAB04" box="[854,956,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Bastanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2308523FFE1FFCDFC3EFA5FFBBFAB04" box="[964,1068,1530,1554]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFEE3F9B8FEE9AB23" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[281,378,1565,1589]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFEE3F9B8FEE9AB23" box="[281,378,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Hersiliola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by its thick, straight, not tapering embolus (filamentous, coiled and tapering in 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFDBCF99AFD34AB41" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[582,679,1599,1623]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFDBCF99AFD34AB41" box="[582,679,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Hersiliola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and massive tegular apophysis (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE1FFCDFBD6F99AFECAAB6C" author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik and Fet 2009: 87</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3.1−3.2). The epigyne in the new genus is also most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFF5AF920FE92AB8B" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[160,257,1669,1693]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFF5AF920FE92AB8B" box="[160,257,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Hersiliola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the two genera can easily be distinguished by the lack of coils of insemination ducts (the insemination duct makes more than one coil, or loop, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE1FFCDFC35F902FBA3ABA9" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[975,1072,1703,1727]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE1FFCDFC35F902FBA3ABA9" box="[975,1072,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1448">Hersiliola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36DB7C1FFE0FFCCFF5AFF2BFDD8AF62" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE0FFCCFF5AFF2BFEB5ADB1" blockId="3.[160,1156,142,479]" box="[160,294,142,167]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">
<heading id="D0805326FFE0FFCCFF5AFF2BFEB5ADB1" box="[160,294,142,167]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" reason="5">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFF5AFF2BFEB5ADB1" bold="true" box="[160,294,142,167]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" reason="3">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE0FFCCFF5AFF17FBFFACC9" blockId="3.[160,1156,142,479]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">
Small-sized, body 5 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFE8CFF17FE10ADDC" box="[374,387,178,202]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">–</emphasis>
7, carapace 2.2 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFDD2FF17FDA6ADDC" box="[552,565,178,202]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">–</emphasis>
2.4 long, 2.3 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFD46FF17FD5AADDC" box="[700,713,178,202]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">–</emphasis>
2.35 wide; carapace slightly longer than wide in females or wider than long in males; leg length formula 2 1 4 3. Cephalic region not elevated; eyes arranged in two rows; posterior median eyes (PME) strongly re-curved; anterior median eyes (AME) larger than other eyes; anterior lateral eyes (ALE), posterior lateral eyes (PLE) and PME subequal in size. Abdomen ovoid in both sexes. Anterior lateral spinnerets shorter than abdomen. Male palp as described in 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE0FFCCFCCAFEFAFC5EAC61" authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[816,973,351,375]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kermanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFCCAFEFAFC5EAC61" box="[816,973,351,375]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">B. kermanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2308523FFE0FFCCFC28FEFAFBB5AC61" box="[978,1062,351,375]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Epigyne without windows, septum wide and high; height of septal lateral arms subequal to septal stem. Insemination duct short, not coiled but only bent, receptacles oval, fertilisation duct as long as receptacle length or longer; accessorial gland large, wider than fertilisation duct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE0FFCCFF5AFDB0FEA5AF38" blockId="3.[160,1155,533,628]" box="[160,310,533,558]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">
<heading id="D0805326FFE0FFCCFF5AFDB0FEA5AF38" box="[160,310,533,558]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" reason="5">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFF5AFDB0FEA5AF38" bold="true" box="[160,310,533,558]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" reason="3">Composition</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE0FFCCFF5AFD9CFDD8AF62" blockId="3.[160,1155,533,628]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">
So far, only two species are considered in the new genus: 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE0FFCCFCC3FD9CFE98AF62" authority="(Marusik and Fet 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Marusik and Fet" baseAuthorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foordi">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFCC3FD9CFC7AAF47" box="[825,1001,569,593]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">Bastanius foordi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE0FFCCFC0DFD9CFE90AF62" author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik and Fet 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE0FFCCFEBDFDF9FE79AF62" authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[327,490,604,628]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kermanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE0FFCCFEBDFDF9FE79AF62" box="[327,490,604,628]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449">B. kermanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2308523FFE0FFCCFE08FDF9FDD8AF62" box="[498,587,604,628]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1449" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
